stylometry:
Allows you to run a simulation before running with a project which can save you money.  It is fairly accurate, especially compared to analytical models.  Helps in communication between model makers and decision makers.  Assists in the decision of the decision makers.
I would use a sim in a business situation because it would allow me to get a good idea what will happen in different situations, and it will allow me to do this without costly testing.  It would allow me to narrow down the ideas that I would want to focus on, and it would let me see possible problems that may arise.
